reviews.text: Fat Moe's Pizza and Wings was a good selection on our Vegas trip.  We kinda just stumbled across the restaurant and were happy we found it.  Nice clean, small restaurant.  Good customer service. The young lady taking orders was very friendly and even suggested a "meal deal" they had going when we visited the restaurant.  Everything was served hot, fresh and was satisfying.  I recommend this restaurant for some tasty quick eats. *side note*  They also had beautiful art for sale on their walls, very cool place.

Support your local family owned businesses! Fat Moe‚Äôs Pizza & Wings isn‚Äôt far from the Vegas strip.

A hella good pizza joint. The staff helped me with my questions and advised something that would be a great choice to split between my friend and I. Because we had dinner reservations later that evening.

We ended up ordering the #7 - 14‚Äù pepperoni pizza, 8 wings (lemon pepper & Honey BBQ) and fries. All of it was really good and the right amount to split for two. I would definitely recommend to others to come by and check out Fat Moe‚Äôs.

Food is great! The mild buffalo was a true mild, so not too spicy for my low tolerance level but great buffalo flavor. Yummy garlic knots and jalapeno poppers as well. My husband said the pizza was great!

After 9 months of no appetite the first thing I craved was some honey Bbq chicken.. we saw this place inline that was right up the street and reviews didn‚Äôt seem bad.. so we placed our order here‚Ä¶ when my husband came home I was itching to open my food.. just to see this underwhelming plate.. they didn‚Äôt even have to time to toss my chicken in the sauce.., the honey bbq it self was very disappointing‚Ä¶kinda taste like Kraft.ü•π  I wanted my husband to take it back but it was time for him to leave for work‚Ä¶

Ordered 3 pizzas delivered cold and flavorless no cheese really terrible.  The wings were decent and were enjoyable.   Meeting with our  delivery person was  such a  adventure.   We waited almost 20 minutes although he claimed he was at the hotel. Our order was missing a beverage, and our desserts were just thrown in the bag. Cheesecake and chocolate cake were all over the place.  Disappointed with the food and service!
